ion. The first known bearer of the surname is a certain Robert <i>de Carsan</i> (or <i>de Acarson</i>), recorded in  1276 ; the ‘de’ suggests derivation from a place name, but no suitable place has been identified. Among Protestants in Northern Ireland, it is sometimes bestowed in honour of  Edward Carson  (  1854–1935 ), the Dublin barrister and politician who was a violent opponent of Home Rule for Ireland. In America the popularity of the name may have been affected by the legendary Missouri frontiersman  Kit Carson  (  1809–68 )."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Garcion II de Lamarque was born in 1150, in Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France as the son of Garcion Ier de Lamarque. He had at least 1 daughter with Thalaise de Blanquefort. He died in 1219, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1150–1219":"1150–1219","1166–1256":"1166–1256","1180–1256":"1180–1256","1110–1154":"1110–1154","1256":"1256","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1150":"1150","1219":"1219","1180":"1180","Lamarque, Lesparre-Médoc,  Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Lamarque, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1150–1219":"1150–1219","1166–1256":"1166–1256","1180–1256":"1180–1256","1110–1154":"1110–1154","1256":"1256","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1150":"1150","1219":"1219","1180":"1180","Lamarque, Lesparre-Médoc,  Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska","Lamarque, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska"},"fr":{"1150–1219":"1150–1219","1166–1256":"1166–1256","1180–1256":"1180–1256","1110–1154":"1110–1154","1256":"1256",